<p><a href="http://i.stack.imgur.com/DGiey.png" rel="nofollow"><img src="http://i.stack.imgur.com/DGiey.png" alt="enter image description here"></a></p>  <hr>  <p>yinitial = x</p>  <p>y_n approaches sqrt(x) as n->infinity</p>  <p>If theres an x input and tol input. Aslong as the |y^2-x| > tol is true compute the following equation of y=0.5*(y + x/y). How would I create a while loop  that will stop when |y^2-x| &lt;= tol. So every time through the loop the y value changes. In order to get this answer---></p>  <pre><code>&gt;&gt;sqrtx = sqRoot(25,100)  sqrtx =  7.4615 </code></pre>  <p>I wrote this so far:</p>  <pre><code>function [sqrtx] = sqrRoot(x,tol)  n = 0; x=0;%initialized variables  if x &gt;=tol %skips all remaining code     return  end  while x &lt;=tol      %code repeated during each loop     x = x+1  %counting code  end </code></pre>